"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The plt.text() function is used to place text at an arbitrary location of the axes, specified by the coordinates. However, the x-coordinate should be a numerical value, not a string. In this case, the date string '2013-01-05' should be converted to a datetime object or a numerical value representing the date on the x-axis.\",\n  \"patch\": \"17c17\\n< plt.text(\\\"2013-01-05\\\", 0.5, \\\"SAMPLE\\\")\\n---\\n> plt.text(datetime.datetime(2013, 1, 5), 0.5, \\\"SAMPLE\\\")\\n\"\n}"